@node "Systemanforderungen" "Requirements"
 @{b}@{u}Requirements:@{ub}@{uu}

- Amiga (ahhh...)

- AmigaOS 3.x

- Ti92

- @{" Linkcable " link "Verbindungskabel" 0}, or the parts for it
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
 @{b}@{u}Installation:@{ub}@{uu}

Nothing easier than that!

Just move the Ti92-Link Drawer where you want to have it - that`s it!
@endnode

@node "Verbindungskabel" "Linkcable"
 @{b}@{u}Linkcable:@{ub}@{uu}

(Neither the cable nor the schematic are done by me.
 There is no waranty of any kind. Have a look at @{" Legal stuff " link "Rechtliches" 0})

I`ve choosen this cable, because I think it`s the most known. (It`s the same
as used by FLINK in @{" Fargo " link "Fargo" 0} on MS-DOS and Linux and it`s the same used by
WinLink on Windoze)


Needed parts:

- 2 silicon diodes

- 1 25pin D-Sub plug (parallel port)

- 1 2.5mm stereo plug
@endnode

