@node "Hauptfenster" "Ti92-Link window"
 @{b}@{u}Mainwindow:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}Screenshot:@{ub} Transfer the screenshot of the calculators display to the Amiga

@{b}FCam screenshot:@{ub} Transfer a screenshot made using the fargoprogram FCamera
(Using FCamera you can create screenshots of @{" fargoprograms " link "Fargo" 0} which also
support grayscales) Start FCamera on the Ti92, start the program of which you
want the screenshot, create the screenshot by pressing the ON key, start
FCamera again, now the screenshot should appear on the display of the Ti92,
press "FCam screenshot" in Ti92-Link followed by pressing the Enter key on the
Ti92. (if there a is a timeouterror directly after pressing "FCam screenshot"
increase Timeout in the settings)

@{b}Save as IFF:@{ub} Saves a screenshot which has been created using "Screenshot" or
"FCam screenshot" before as IFF-ILBM picture.@{b}

Create Romdump:@{ub} Transfer the Ti92 romimage using the  Fargoprogram  Romdump
into a file which could be used for a Ti92-Emulator (but as much as I know
there doesn`t exist one for Amiga, if I`m wrong please tell @{" me " link "Autor" 0}) The romsize
can be changed in the settingswindow since I don`t know if 1024kb is the only
romsize which exists. (If somebody knows if there is only this romsize, or if
somebody knows of other romsizes please tell @{" me " link "Autor" 0}) Note: On my Ti92 (ROM
v1.12) the Romdump-program of Frago I doesn`t work correct, but the one from
Fargo II works.

@{b}Receive:@{ub} Has the same function as like "Receive" in the Var-Link Window on the
Ti92. Select Vars on Ti92, press "Receive" in Ti92-Link followed by selecting
"send" in the menu on the Ti92 (if there a is a timeouterror directly after
pressing "Receive" increase Timeout in the settings)

@{b}Check calculator:@{ub} Checks if the calculator is ready. If not effectful there
could be something wrong with the Linkcable. (In Fargo the calculator won`t
answer) If the calculator is ready, but not at "Homescreen" it`s for example
not possible to transfer Vars from the Amiga to the calculator. To get back to
the Homescreen press the green key at the right side of the ON key and Q.

@{b}Create backup:@{ub} Creates a Backupfile (#?.92b) of the Memory of the calculator,
so also the settings on the calculator can be saved.

@{b}Send backup:@{ub} Sends a Backupfile (#?.92b) back to the calculator. (The are
backups in the Internet which include a preinstalled @{" Fargokernel " link "Fargo" 0})

@{b}Remote:@{ub} To control the Ti92 using the Amigakeyboard. (Doesn`t work in Fargo)
You can choose in the settings if only the keys get transfered or if there
also screenshots of the Ti92 display get transfered.

@{b}Load file:@{ub} Loads a file which contains Vars (#?.92p, #?.92g) and displays them
as a list.

@{b}Update list:@{ub} Updates the list which contains the names of the Vars on the
Ti92.

@{b}<--:@{ub} Transfers the Var selected in the "Vars on TI-92" list onto the Amiga.

@{b}-->:@{ub} Transfers the Var selected in the "Vars on Amiga" list onto the Ti92.

@{b}<==:@{ub} Transfers all Vars in the "Vars on TI-92" list onto the Amiga.

@{b}==>:@{ub} Transfers all Vars in the "Vars on Amiga" list onto the Ti92.

@{b}Save to file:@{ub} Saves the Vars in the "Vars on Amiga" list into a file (#?.92p,
#?.92g)

@{b}Show:@{ub} Shows the TEXT or PIC Var which is selected in the "Vars on Amiga" list.
(The used Text- and Pictureviewers can be changed in the Settingswindow)

@{b}Settings:@{ub} Opens the Settingswindow.
@endnode

